    body: 'The Resurrection is not only a historical event but the ontological foundation of the new creation. In mystical theology, the risen Christ is the first fruits of the transformed humanity to which all mystics aspire. The resurrection of the body reveals that mystical union is not an escape from matter but its transfiguration. Those who share in Christ\'s death through the dark night will share in His risen life.',
    whyItMatters: 'The Resurrection assures the mystic that the path of dying to self is not futile but leads to a fullness of life beyond imagination.',
