    body: 'The Ascension brings glorified human nature into the very heart of the Trinity, as the risen Christ takes His place at the Father\'s right hand. Mystical theology sees in this event the promise that humanity is destined for divinization. The Ascension also inaugurates a new mode of Christ\'s presence — hidden, spiritual, and sacramental — which is the context for all subsequent mystical experience in the Church.',
    whyItMatters: 'The Ascension reveals that human nature has been elevated to the highest dignity, and that the mystic\'s longing for God is not in vain but will find eternal fulfillment.',
