    body: 'At Pentecost, the Holy Spirit descended upon the apostles in tongues of fire, empowering them for mission and inaugurating the Church\'s mystical life. Pentecost is the ongoing source of all charismatic and contemplative gifts in the Church. The Spirit who fell upon the apostles continues to fill believers with gifts of prayer, wisdom, and love, enabling the mystical encounter with God that is the birthright of every baptized Christian.',
    whyItMatters: 'Pentecost affirms that the mystical life is not reserved for the few but is the Spirit\'s gift to the entire Church, empowering every believer for communion with God.',
