    oneLiner: 'The manifestations of God in the Old Testament as foundational paradigms for understanding mystical experience.',
    body: 'Theophanies — visible or perceptible manifestations of God — occur throughout the Old Testament: the burning bush, the pillar of fire and cloud, the Sinai theophany, Elijah\'s encounter at Horeb, and Isaiah\'s vision of the Lord in the Temple. These events established the vocabulary and categories that Christian mystics would later use to describe their own encounters with God. Each theophany reveals different aspects of God\'s nature: holiness, transcendence, mercy, and glory.',
    whyItMatters: 'Biblical theophanies provide the normative framework for evaluating and understanding mystical experiences, anchoring personal encounter in the public revelation of Scripture.',
