    body: 'The Hebrew word kabod signifies the "weight" or "glory" of God\'s manifest presence, experienced as overwhelming light, cloud, and power. When the glory of the Lord filled Solomon\'s Temple, the priests could not stand to minister (1 Kings 8:11). In Christian mysticism, the kabod is understood as the radiance of God\'s being that mystics glimpse in contemplation and that will be fully revealed in the beatific vision.',
    whyItMatters: 'The concept of kabod reminds the mystic that God\'s self-revelation is not abstract but weighty and transformative, demanding awe and total surrender.',
