    body: 'Catholic mystical theology teaches that suffering is not meaningless but can be transformed by grace into a participation in Christ\'s redemptive work. St. John Paul II\'s apostolic letter Salvifici Doloris explored this mystery, affirming that suffering united to Christ becomes a source of grace for the whole Church. Mystics who embrace redemptive suffering discover within it a paradoxical joy and a profound intimacy with the Crucified Lord.',
    whyItMatters: 'Redemptive suffering offers the ultimate answer to the problem of pain, revealing that suffering freely offered in love has the power to save souls.',
    relatedTerms: ['myst-victim-soul', 'myst-co-suffering-with-christ', 'myst-offering-of-suffering'],
