    term: 'Offering of Suffering',
    category: 'mysticism',
    tags: ['offering', 'suffering', 'prayer'],
    oneLiner: 'The deliberate spiritual act of offering one\'s sufferings to God in union with Christ for a particular intention.',
    body: 'The offering of suffering is a fundamental practice in Catholic spiritual life, in which the believer consciously unites their pain — physical, emotional, or spiritual — with the sacrifice of Christ on the Cross, directing it toward a specific intention such as the conversion of sinners or the relief of souls in purgatory. This practice is rooted in the theology of the Mystical Body and the communion of saints. It transforms passive suffering into an active, redemptive offering of love.',
    whyItMatters: 'Offering suffering empowers every Christian to participate in Christ\'s redemptive mission, making even the most ordinary pains a source of supernatural fruitfulness.',
