    oneLiner: 'The mystical significance of the 1858 apparitions at Lourdes, where Mary identified herself as the Immaculate Conception.',
    body: 'In 1858, the Blessed Virgin Mary appeared eighteen times to St. Bernadette Soubirous in a grotto at Lourdes, France. Mary identified herself as "the Immaculate Conception," confirming the dogma defined just four years earlier. A miraculous spring was revealed at the site, and Lourdes became one of the greatest pilgrimage destinations in the world, known for physical and spiritual healings. The message of Lourdes emphasizes prayer, penance, and trust in God\'s mercy.',
