    body: 'Catholic spiritual writers consistently teach that Mary plays an active role in the formation of the interior life of believers. As the one who formed Christ physically in her womb, she forms Him spiritually in the souls of the faithful. This maternal action includes inspiring prayer, guiding discernment, strengthening virtue, and protecting against temptation. St. Louis de Montfort taught that the Holy Spirit works most effectively in souls who are most united to Mary.',
