    body: 'Angelic mysticism encompasses the rich Catholic tradition of understanding the role of angels in the spiritual life. Drawing on Scripture, Pseudo-Dionysius the Areopagite, and St. Thomas Aquinas, this tradition teaches that angels are pure spirits who serve as God\'s messengers, protectors, and instruments of illumination. Mystics have reported encounters with angels that bring guidance, consolation, and protection on the path to God.',
